{"pageProps":{"eyebrow":"AgentSight","page":{"layout":"document","title":"Usage","description":"1. Clone the repository and initialize submodules","descriptionIsExcerpt":true,"bodyHtml":"<p><strong>English</strong> | <a href=\"https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/agentsight/blob/master/docs/usage.zh-CN.md\">中文</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"building-from-source\">Building from Source</h2>\n<h3 id=\"1-clone-the-repository-and-initialize-submodules\">1. Clone the repository and initialize submodules</h3>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">git</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> clone</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/agentsight.git</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">cd</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> agentsight</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">git</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> submodule</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> update</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> --init</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> --recursive</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<p>If you have already cloned the repository but the submodule directories (<code>libbpf/</code> and <code>bpftool/</code>) are empty, run:</p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">git</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> submodule</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> update</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> --init</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> --recursive</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<h3 id=\"2-install-system-dependencies\">2. Install system dependencies</h3>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">make</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> install</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<p>This installs the required build dependencies: libelf, zlib, clang, llvm, Node.js, and the Rust toolchain.</p>\n<h3 id=\"3-build\">3. Build</h3>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">make</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> build</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<p>After a successful build, the agentsight binary is located at <code>collector/target/release/agentsight</code>.</p>\n<p>You can also build individual components:</p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">make</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> build-bpf</span><span style=\"color:#768390\">       # eBPF C programs only</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">make</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> build-rust</span><span style=\"color:#768390\">      # Rust collector only</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">make</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> build-frontend</span><span style=\"color:#768390\">  # Frontend only</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<h2 id=\"running-from-source\">Running from Source</h2>\n<p>Navigate to the repository root after <code>make build</code>. Commands that load eBPF\nprobes should be run with <code>sudo</code>; AgentSight can request sudo if you forget, but\nexplicit sudo is the recommended path.</p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\"># Live view of local agent sessions</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">sudo</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> ./collector/target/release/agentsight</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> top</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"> </span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\"># Launch and record a command</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">sudo</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> ./collector/target/release/agentsight</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> record</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> --</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> claude</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"> </span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\"># Attach to an already-running process family</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">sudo</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> ./collector/target/release/agentsight</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> record</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> -c</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> claude</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"> </span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\"># Debug-level configurable tracing</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">sudo</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> ./collector/target/release/agentsight</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> debug</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> trace</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> --server</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> -c</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> claude</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"> </span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\"># Raw SSL debug capture with HTTP parsing</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">sudo</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> ./collector/target/release/agentsight</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> debug</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> ssl</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> --http-parser</span></span></code></pre></figure>","headings":[{"id":"building-from-source","text":"Building from Source","depth":2},{"id":"1-clone-the-repository-and-initialize-submodules","text":"1. Clone the repository and initialize submodules","depth":3},{"id":"2-install-system-dependencies","text":"2. Install system dependencies","depth":3},{"id":"3-build","text":"3. Build","depth":3},{"id":"running-from-source","text":"Running from Source","depth":2}],"sourcePath":"https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/eunomia.dev/tree/main/docs/agentsight/quickstart.md","metadata":{"updatedAt":"2026-06-03T07:29:58.000Z","createdAt":"2026-06-02T03:15:25.000Z","authors":[{"name":"LinuxDev9002","email":"linuxdev8883@example.com"}]},"path":"/agentsight/quickstart/","alternates":{"en":"/agentsight/quickstart/","zh":"/zh/agentsight/quickstart/"},"continuation":{"index":{"title":"AgentSight: System-wide AI agent tracing and monitoring with eBPF","description":"![License: MIT](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT) ![CI](https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/agentsight/actions/workflows/ci.yml) ![arXiv:2508.02736](https://arxiv.org/abs/2508.02736) ![DOI:10.1145/3766882.3767169](https://","href":"/agentsight/"},"previous":{"title":"OpenTelemetry GenAI Export","description":"AgentSight can export the LLM calls it captures as OpenTelemetry GenAI semantic-convention (genai.) spans, sent to any OpenTelemetry Collector over OTLP/HTTP. Because AgentSight reconstructs the traffic from the kernel (","href":"/agentsight/otel/"}},"sidebar":[{"title":"AgentSight","items":[{"title":"Overview","href":"/agentsight/"},{"title":"Quick start","href":"/agentsight/quickstart/"},{"title":"Supported agents","href":"/agentsight/agents/"},{"title":"Build from source","href":"/agentsight/build/"},{"title":"Docker","href":"/agentsight/docker/"},{"title":"OpenTelemetry","href":"/agentsight/otel/"},{"title":"Development","href":"/agentsight/development/"}]}]}},"__N_SSG":true}